 <p><p> <img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg" border="0"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2036<br> <font color=#333333>(10/4/02 11:07:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1039.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Simple Horse Question</span><hr size=1> I have the 100K ponee, and have never regretted it for a moment.  While standing mana regeneration and access to spell books is all well and good, and certainly worth 10K, the ability to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;make like a banana and split.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has saved my bacon a number of times.  For example, I hunt deep inside <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SkyFire</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> where no one else does.  About once a week, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Talendor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> spawns.  Since I have been hunting there off and on for many levels and even more AA, let's just say <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mister Tee</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and I don't get along, and leave it at that.  He has an enormous aggro range, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SkyFire</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is all spires and valleys.  Luckily, when he surprises me, it's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Hi ho, Tanqueray, away!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and I run across this enormous zone for the exit.<br>
<br>
It makes new strategies available to me.  I farm <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Chromadracs</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for experience and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Essence of Sunlight</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which I use for smithing.  If you stand around in one place, and start killing chromas, pretty soon there are no more chromas there.  So I do something I call <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;The Lonesome Cowboy.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  I ride around the interior of the zone with no pet.  When I find a chroma, I lasso that little doggie with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Malosini</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and herd it to the zone wall, where I summon a pet and kill me a chroma.  I could not do that without my trusty steed <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Tanqueray</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
One thing to beware of.  Your pet <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>will</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> be jealous of your horse.  You will notice that your pet is always staring right at your horse.<br>
<br>
My advice is to either get the 10K or the 100K, and nothing in between.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulofwyr123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lofwyr123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#333333>(10/5/02 7:27:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1039.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Simple Horse Question</span><hr size=1> Ok Raz, i follow you there and agree on the 10 or 100 the middle is junk.  Here is two things.  First off, do you think its worth buying the 10k for the effect while you save up 100 for the higher one?  Also, do you think with run 3 being faster than the lowest horse it would lose any sort of utility in that respect making the higher one even more valuble comparativly.  Seeing as this is about the last thing I may save up for, a few things aside like smithing stuff etc etc, I am wondering if the effect is worth the inital purpose since 10k is far easier to obtain than 100, or if it would actually be less useful due to speed issues that it would hamper things despite the benefits.  Far as I can tell for static camp areas it would be worth it but hurt you in an area such as sf where mobility is needed.  Not sure how that pans out in terms of total usefulness, but I tend to do static areas more .. I think.  Will have to evaluate it further.<br>
<br>
Lofwyr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2040<br> <font color=#333333>(10/5/02 3:37:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1039.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Simple Horse Question</span><hr size=1> Since 10K is far easier for you to obtain than 100K, I that argues in favor of the 10K ponee now.  I get varying reports on how fast the 10K ponee is, but you can always click it off and run, if it is not as fast.<br>
<br>
The fact that you can meditate and access while standing is well worth 10K.  Not only do you not have to make the decision to sit or stand, which makes play more relaxing, you avoid sitting aggro.  When you sell the 10K ponee finally, you will lose about 3K.  If it takes a while to get your 100K, then think of the 3K as a down payment, or alternately rent until then.<br>
<br>
Mages generally prefer static camps, and do not kite, so the 10K ponee will likely fit in with your style.  For escape, if the ponee is too slow, dismount and run.  I suspect the ponee is not nearly as fast as JBoots or Run 3, despite some reports to the contrary.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
